WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.480
Hi I'm Karan. I'm a QA engineer on the Shiny team. Shiny is a web development framework that people

00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:13.840
can use irrespective of their technical expertise to create really good looking dashboards. If

00:00:13.840 --> 00:00:20.080
you're using it for prototyping or you're using it for production ready dashboards, you can use it.

00:00:20.080 --> 00:00:27.040
So Shiny works in R as well as Python. So if you have some things, your workflows that you

00:00:27.040 --> 00:00:32.720
are using R packages or Python packages, it should integrate seamlessly. Shiny can be used

00:00:32.720 --> 00:00:38.959
for making more than dashboards. You can make fully functional apps. You can make user surveys.

00:00:39.759 --> 00:00:46.480
You can make a sorting app. People associate Shiny with dashboards but Shiny is way more than that.

00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:52.320
Anything that you would want to do in a Python ecosystem or an R ecosystem but just have a

00:00:52.320 --> 00:00:59.119
fancy front end, you can do it in Shiny. To get started, you can go to the Posit website to find

00:00:59.119 --> 00:01:05.760
out more about Shiny. You can install the packages. They are on CRAN as well as on PyPI

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:07.839
to install and get started.

